---
import DocsLayout from "../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Python SDK">
  <h1>Python SDK Reference</h1>
  <p>
    The Python SDK (<code>entdb-sdk</code>) is a type-safe async client for
    EntDB. It is <strong>proto-first</strong> &mdash; you define your schema in
    a <code>.proto</code> file, compile it with the standard
    <code>protoc</code>, and register the generated module with the SDK. No
    custom codegen.
  </p>

  <h2>Installation</h2>
  <pre is:raw><code>pip install entdb-sdk</code></pre>

  <h2>Proto-First Workflow</h2>
  <p>
    Define your types once in a <code>.proto</code> file. Every message you
    want to store as a node needs a stable <code>type_id</code> option, and
    every field uses its protobuf field number as the on-disk
    <code>field_id</code>.
  </p>
  <pre is:raw><code>// schema.proto
syntax = "proto3";
package myapp;

import "entdb/options.proto";

message Task {
  option (entdb.type_id) = 1;

  string title = 1;
  string status = 2;   // "todo" | "in_progress" | "done"
  int32 priority = 3;
}

message Comment {
  option (entdb.type_id) = 3;
  string body = 1;
}</code></pre>

  <p>Compile with the standard protoc &mdash; no EntDB-specific codegen.</p>
  <pre is:raw><code>protoc --python_out=. schema.proto</code></pre>

  <p>Register the generated module with the SDK:</p>
  <pre is:raw><code>from entdb_sdk import DbClient, register_proto_schema
import schema_pb2

registry = register_proto_schema(schema_pb2)</code></pre>

  <h2>TypedNode Dataclasses</h2>
  <p>
    For ergonomic access to node payloads, wrap proto messages in a
    <code>TypedNode</code> dataclass. <code>to_payload()</code> and
    <code>from_payload()</code> handle the conversion to and from the
    field-id-keyed wire form.
  </p>
  <pre is:raw><code>from dataclasses import dataclass
from entdb_sdk import TypedNode
import schema_pb2

@dataclass
class Task(TypedNode[schema_pb2.Task]):
    proto_cls = schema_pb2.Task

task = Task(title="Ship v2", status="todo")
payload = task.to_payload()     # {"1": "Ship v2", "2": "todo"}
restored = Task.from_payload(payload)</code></pre>

  <h2>Connecting</h2>
  <pre is:raw><code>from entdb_sdk import DbClient

async with DbClient(
    "localhost:50051",
    api_key="your-key",
    secure=True,
    registry=registry,
) as db:
    ...</code></pre>

  <h3>Constructor Options</h3>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    <tr><td><code>address</code></td><td>str</td><td>&mdash;</td><td>Server address (host:port)</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>secure</code></td><td>bool</td><td>False</td><td>Use TLS</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>api_key</code></td><td>str | None</td><td>None</td><td>Scoped API key for auth</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>max_retries</code></td><td>int</td><td>3</td><td>Max retries on transient failures</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>registry</code></td><td>SchemaRegistry | None</td><td>None</td><td>Schema registry from <code>register_proto_schema()</code></td></tr>
  </table>

  <h2>Typed Primitives</h2>

  <h3>Actor</h3>
  <p>
    An <code>Actor</code> is a typed principal identifier that replaces raw
    <code>"user:bob"</code> strings throughout the SDK.
  </p>
  <pre is:raw><code>from entdb_sdk import Actor

Actor.user("alice")         # user:alice
Actor.group("admins")       # group:admins
Actor.service("ingest-api") # service:ingest-api</code></pre>

  <h3>Permission</h3>
  <pre is:raw><code>from entdb_sdk import Permission

Permission.READ
Permission.WRITE
Permission.ADMIN</code></pre>

  <h3>ACLEntry</h3>
  <pre is:raw><code>from entdb_sdk import ACLEntry, Actor, Permission

entry = ACLEntry(
    grantee=Actor.user("bob"),
    permission=Permission.WRITE,
)</code></pre>

  <h2>Hierarchical Scope API</h2>
  <p>
    Bind tenant and actor once with <code>db.tenant(...).actor(...)</code>
    instead of passing them on every call.
  </p>
  <pre is:raw><code>scope = db.tenant("acme").actor(Actor.user("alice"))

task = await scope.get(Task, node_id)
tasks = await scope.query(Task, filter={"status": "todo"}, limit=20)

plan = scope.plan()
plan.create(schema_pb2.Task(title="New", status="todo"))
result = await plan.commit(wait_applied=True)</code></pre>

  <h2>Plans (Atomic Transactions)</h2>
  <p>
    <code>Plan.create()</code> now accepts proto messages directly &mdash; the
    SDK uses the registered schema to translate field names to field IDs at
    the boundary.
  </p>
  <pre is:raw><code>import schema_pb2

plan = db.tenant("acme").actor(Actor.user("alice")).plan()

task_ref = plan.create(schema_pb2.Task(title="Ship v2", status="todo"), as_="t")
comment_ref = plan.create(schema_pb2.Comment(body="Let's ship it"), as_="c")
plan.edge_create(HasComment, from_="$t.id", to="$c.id")

plan.update(Task, node_id, {"status": "done"})
plan.delete(Task, old_id)

result = await plan.commit(wait_applied=True)
task_id = result.created_node_ids[0]</code></pre>

  <h3>CommitResult</h3>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    <tr><td><code>success</code></td><td>bool</td><td>Whether commit succeeded</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>receipt</code></td><td>Receipt</td><td>Transaction receipt with stream_position</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>created_node_ids</code></td><td>list[str]</td><td>IDs of created nodes (in order)</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>applied</code></td><td>bool</td><td>Whether event was applied (if wait_applied)</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>error</code></td><td>str | None</td><td>Error message on failure</td></tr>
  </table>

  <h2>ACL Operations</h2>
  <pre is:raw><code>scope = db.tenant("acme").actor(Actor.user("alice"))

# Share
await scope.share(node_id, Actor.user("bob"), Permission.WRITE)

# Revoke
await scope.revoke(node_id, Actor.user("bob"))

# Shared with me
nodes = await scope.shared_with_me(limit=50)

# Group membership
await db.tenant("acme").group_add(Actor.group("eng"), Actor.user("alice"))
await db.tenant("acme").group_remove(Actor.group("eng"), Actor.user("alice"))

# Ownership transfer
await scope.transfer_ownership(node_id, Actor.user("bob"))</code></pre>

  <h2>Read-after-Write Consistency</h2>
  <p>
    The SDK automatically tracks the last observed stream offset per tenant
    in <code>db._last_offsets</code> and forwards it on subsequent reads. You
    usually do not need to manage offsets yourself.
  </p>
  <pre is:raw><code># Automatic — the SDK remembers the offset from the previous commit
await plan.commit()
task = await scope.get(Task, node_id)   # guaranteed to see the write

# Explicit control is still available
result = await plan.commit()
task = await scope.get(Task, node_id,
                       after_offset=result.receipt.stream_position)

await db.wait_for_offset("acme", result.receipt.stream_position, timeout=5.0)</code></pre>

  <h2>GDPR Operations</h2>
  <p>
    These operations are scoped by <code>user_id</code> (the global user
    identifier, e.g. <code>"alice"</code>), not by
    <code>tenant_principal</code>.
  </p>
  <pre is:raw><code># Soft delete with a grace window — cancellable
await db.delete_user("alice", grace_period_days=30)
await db.cancel_user_deletion("alice")

# Export all of a user's data across all tenants (right of access / portability)
export = await db.export_user_data("alice")

# Freeze (suspend) a user — blocks writes without deleting data
await db.freeze_user("alice", reason="legal hold")</code></pre>

  <p>
    Each of these calls appends an event to the WAL, so they show up in the
    compliance audit trail. See
    <a href="/tenant-shard-db/docs/compliance/audit">Compliance &amp; Audit</a>
    for details on Object Lock and crypto-shred.
  </p>

  <h2>Error Handling</h2>
  <pre is:raw><code>from entdb_sdk import (
    ConnectionError,
    ValidationError,
    SchemaError,
    UnknownFieldError,
    AccessDeniedError,
    NotFoundError,
)

try:
    plan.create(schema_pb2.Task(title="x"))
    await plan.commit()
except UnknownFieldError as e:
    print(e)  # "Unknown field 'foo' on Task. Did you mean: title?"
except AccessDeniedError as e:
    print(e.actor, e.required_permission)
except ConnectionError as e:
    print(e.address)</code></pre>
</DocsLayout>
